dct_description_sm: Relief shown by contours, hachures, and spot heights; depths shown by soundings.
Shows drainage, named streets, buildings, railroads, etc.
"Triangulation and topography by A.W. Chase, Assistant in 1875; hydrography by H.C. Taylor, Lieut. Comdr., U.S.N. Assistant in 1875."
Oriented with north toward upper left.
Series no. 668 crossed out and 5149 stamped as a replacement number.
